TY  - JOUR
AU  - Décaire, Paul H
AU  - Gilje, Erik P
AU  - Taillard, Jérôme P
T1  - Real Option Exercise: Empirical Evidence
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhz092
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 33
IS  - 7
SP  - 3250
EP  - 3306
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study when and why firms exercise real options. Using detailed project-level investment data, we find that the likelihood that a firm exercises a real option is strongly related to peer exercise behavior. Peer exercise decisions are as important in explaining exercise behavior as variables commonly associated with standard real option theories, such as volatility. We identify peer effects using localized exogenous variation in peer project exercise decisions and find evidence consistent with information externalities being important for exercise behavior. (JEL G30, G31, G32)
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhz092
ER  - 



